    I - input symbol type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<I>, Collection<I>, Comparator<I>, IntFunction<I>, ToIntFunction<I>, List<I>, ArrayWritable<I>, Alphabet<I>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GrowingMapAlphabet

    public class MapAlphabet<I>
extends AbstractAlphabet<I>
    A map-based alphabet implementation, that does not impose any restriction on the input symbol class. This implementation stores the alphabet symbols in a List for fast idx to symbol look-ups as well as a Map for fast symbol to idx look-ups.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
